      "writtenOn": "2021-06-18T02:15:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is the case where a local fixture is linked to both a local bundle and a remote bundle.\n\nThis can happen sometimes because it\u0027s too easy to link a fixture to a bundle (just importing the package). For tests we avoid unintentional links by forbidding imports between bundle packages (i.e. it is forbidden by tast-lint to import chromiumos/tast/{local,remote}/bundles/$bundle/$category package from anywhere). However, fixtures are defined usually in support packages, so it\u0027s undesirable but possible that a fixture is accidentally linked.\n\nI\u0027m not sure if the current approach to disambiguate a fixture is the best. We may want to enforce import rules more strictly to avoid accidental linkage of fixtures. But currently the framework has a workaround to choose from the two.",
      "parentUuid": "6b002df4_44cc8ada",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 218,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 221,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "676576d4403df9ec829f090acef7a9b54bac56b9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
